@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-4">

    <h2 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy</h2>

    <p>
        At HRMS (Human Resource Management System), we value your privacy and are committed
        to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
        use, and safeguard your data within our system.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
    <p>
        We collect employee-related information such as name, email address, phone number,
        department, designation, salary, and attendance details to manage HR operations effectively.
    </p>

    <h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <p>
        The collected data is used for:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Managing employee records</li>
        <li>Tracking attendance and performance</li>
        <li>Processing leave requests</li>
        <li>Internal reporting and HR operations</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Data Security</h4>
    <p>
        We implement appropriate security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access,
        alteration, or disclosure. Only authorized personnel (HR/Admin) have access to sensitive information.
    </p>

    <h4>4. Data Sharing</h4>
    <p>
        We do not share employee data with third parties except when required by law or for
        organizational purposes.
    </p>

    <h4>5. User Responsibility</h4>
    <p>
        Employees are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their login credentials
        and should not share their passwords with others.
    </p>

    <h4>6. Updates to Policy</h4>
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page.
    </p>

    <h4>7. Contact Us</h4>
    <p>
        If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact your HR department.
    </p>

</div>